# ESP32-C6 Robot Car
## Components
* ESP32-C6
* L298N H-Bridge
* 4 DC Motors
* HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
* SG90 Servo Motor
* External Battery Pack

---

# DC Motor Connections (L298N)

## ESP32-C6 → L298N

| ESP32 GPIO | L298N |
| ---------- | ----- |
| GPIO12     | IN1   |
| GPIO13     | IN2   |
| GPIO11     | IN3   |
| GPIO10     | IN4   |

## L298N → Motors

| L298N       | Motor Side   |
| ----------- | ------------ |
| OUT1 + OUT2 | Left motors  |
| OUT3 + OUT4 | Right motors |

Two left motors are connected in parallel.

Two right motors are connected in parallel.

## Power

| Connection | Target           |
| ---------- | ---------------- |
| Battery +  | L298N VIN / +12V |
| Battery -  | L298N GND        |
| ESP32 GND  | L298N GND        |

Important: ESP32 and L298N must share the same GND.

---

# Ultrasonic Sensor (HC-SR04)

| HC-SR04 | ESP32  |
| ------- | ------ |
| VCC     | 5V     |
| GND     | GND    |
| TRIG    | GPIO21 |
| ECHO    | GPIO20 |

The ultrasonic sensor measures the distance in front of the robot.

---

# Servo Motor (SG90)

| Servo Wire      | ESP32 |
| --------------- | ----- |
| Signal (Orange) | GPIO8 |
| VCC (Red)       | 5V    |
| GND (Brown)     | GND   |

The servo rotates the ultrasonic sensor to scan left and right.

---

# Software Modules

## motor.c

Controls:

* Forward
* Backward
* Left turn
* Right turn
* Stop

---

## servo.c

Controls:

* Servo initialization
* Servo angle (0° to 180°)

---

## ultrasonic.c

Controls:

* Trigger pulse
* Echo measurement
* Distance calculation in centimeters

---

# Main Goal

The robot car should:

1. Move forward.
2. Measure distance using the ultrasonic sensor.
3. Turn the servo to scan left and right.
4. Decide the best direction.
5. Avoid obstacles automatically.


